New York Mayor Bill de Blasio says he wants to see an outlined vision of where Hillary Clinton plans to go before giving up an endorsement for her presidential campaign .
As campaign manager for Clinton 's successful 2000 Senate run , de Blasio said on Sunday it is important for her to define her campaign message , and he wants her vision for addressing income inequality .
De Blasio says the income inequality in the U.S. is ` out of control .